Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%grams} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm wide fries (no need to peel).

Pop the fries onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with oil, season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2} (or use a garlic press). Halve, peel and chop the @echalion shallot{1} into small pieces.

Cut the @lemon{1} into wedges. Roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{1%bunch}(roughly chopped) (stalks and all).

Halve the @baby plum tomatoes{125%grams}.

In a large #bowl{}, combine the @cider vinegar{15%ml}, @sugar{1%tsp} and @olive oil{1%tbsp} for the dressing. Season with salt and pepper. Set your salad dressing aside.

When your chips are halfway through cooking, place the @demi garlic baguettes{2} on a medium #baking tray{}.

Bake on the middle shelf of your oven until golden and piping hot, ~{12-15%minutes}.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of oil in a large #saucepan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the shallot and cook until softened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Stir in the garlic and fry until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Add the @garlic & white wine Scottish mussels{500%grams} and their liquid into the pan. Pop the lid on and cook until piping hot, ~{5%minutes}. Discard any mussels that do not open.

> IMPORTANT: Ensure the mussels are piping hot throughout.

Stir the @creme fraiche{75%grams} into the saucepan and bring to a simmer. Simmer until thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir in a good squeeze of lemon juice and half the parsley.

When everything's ready, add the tomatoes and @baby leaf mix{50%grams} to the dressing and toss to coat.

Share the mussels between your serving #bowls{} and sprinkle over the remaining parsley.

Serve your frites, salad and garlic baguettes alongside.

Serve with the @mayonnaise{64%grams} for dipping and any remaining lemon wedges for squeezing over.

Enjoy!